  "url": "https://www.ada.lk/breaking_news/\u0db4\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dc0\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca-\u0dc4\u0dbd\u0dda-\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0da7-\u0dc4\u0dcf--\u0d9a\u0dc5\u0db8\u0db1\u0dcf\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0da7-\u0d9c\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca-\u0dc3\u0dd9\u0db6\u0dc5\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca-\u0db8\u0dbb\u0dab\u0dd3\u0dba-\u0dad\u0dbb\u0dca\u0da2\u0db1/11-395168",
  "time_ut": 1657101301,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dc0\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca \u0dc4\u0dbd\u0dda \u0dc4\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0da7 \u0dc4\u0dcf  \u0d9a\u0dc5\u0db8\u0db1\u0dcf\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0da7 \u0d9c\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc3\u0dd9\u0db6\u0dc5\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0db8\u0dbb\u0dab\u0dd3\u0dba \u0dad\u0dbb\u0dca\u0da2\u0db1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The owner and manager of the filling station received death threats from airmen",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Piliyandala Police said that a group of soldiers from the Ratmalana Air Force Base stormed into the Sipetco petrol station in Piliyandala Miriswatta in two jeeps and threatened the owner and manager of the petrol station with death.",
        "It is mentioned in the complaint that this threat was made based on an incident where the air force soldiers who were deployed to guard the fuel station from about a week ago, were knocked on the body of several soldiers by a fuel station employee at night while they were staying and sleeping in the same fuel room on the last night.",
        "Police say that on the 30th, five officers from the Ratmalana military base attached to the Sri Lanka Air Force came to guard our fuel station.",
        "On the second day, an air force officer told me that the boy working in the shed was not letting the people sleep, and was beating them. I told them that I will fire that worker, then they told me that they would take that worker to the camp and threaten to beat him.",
        "And they told me that you should write a letter willingly and that you don't need security. I said no. At the same time, the officer raised his hand to hit me and threatened that he would not let me in.",
        "The scenes of scolding and trying to hit me are also recorded on my mobile phone. Also, it has been recorded in the CCTV cameras installed in the petrol station.",
        "There was an argument between our fuel shop manager and an air force officer regarding knocking a sleeping person.",
        "I heard the officer telling someone about it on the phone. After about twenty minutes, a group of men and women wearing commando uniforms came to the petrol station in two jeeps. I was in the office of the petrol station at that time.",
        "Three officials who came in this way threatened to kill them and said that they have taken over the fuel station and they have to work as they say.",
        "Also, they threatened me and said that they could kill me, shoot me, pick me up and hit me on the ground and kept threatening me, said the complaint filed by the owner.",
        "It is also stated in her complaint that the relevant incident was recorded on the CCTV cameras installed at the petrol station.",
        "The complaint further states that he informed a senior officer of the Ratmalana Air Force Base over the phone regarding the relevant death threat.",
        "On the advice of Senior Superintendent of Police Mangala Dehideniya and Assistant Superintendent of Police Sarnath Samarakoon in charge of Mt.Piliyandala Police, Chief Inspector of Police Sanath Ranjith is conducting investigations."
      ],
